<div class="panel-group" id="accordion" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">
  <div class="panel panel-default">
    <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingOne">
      <h4 class="panel-title">
        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#oauthAuthorize" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
          oauth#authorize - Ask for access grant code on behalf of the user
        </a>
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div id="oauthAuthorize" class="panel-collapse collapse in" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingOne">
      <div class="panel-body">

        <p>
          If users are logged into HackCentral and give your app permisison, we will send them back to [redirect_uri] together with an access_grant token as code parameter.
          Use this access_grant in the oauth#token step.
        </p>

        <p>HTTP Request: <code>GET http://api.hackcentral.co/v1/oauth/authorize</code></p>

        <p>Query Parameters:</p>

        <table class="table table-striped">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Parameter</th>
              <th>Required</th>
              <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>client_id</td>
              <td>true</td>
              <td>The id of your application</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>redirect_uri</td>
              <td>true</td>
              <td>Where shall we redirect the client afterwards to?</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>response_type</td>
              <td>true</td>
              <td>The parameter name of the request token that will be passed to your site, in case of doubt use <code>code</code></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <div id="request">
          <h3>Request:</h3>

          <strong>Route:</strong>
          <p>
            <code>
              GET /v1/oauth/authorize?client_id=b851c6b8b04e9befcb536ede00405e69ad3782678c1e13981035b3bac66924f7
              &redirect_uri=http%3A%2F%2Fexample.org%2F&response_type=code
            </code>
          </p>

          <strong>Headers:</strong>
          <p>
            <code>
              Host: api.hackcentral.co
            </code>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div id="response">
          <h3>Response:</h3>

          <strong>Status:</strong>
          <p>
            <code>
              200 OK
            </code>
          </p>

          <strong>Headers:</strong>
          <code>
            X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
            X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block
            X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
            Content-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8
            ETag: W/"ed8ff432635c36e9c228754a606432d0"
            Cache-Control: max-age=0, private, must-revalidate
            Content-Length: 2304
          </code>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
